-- Jordan Finds Phosphate Reserves Worth $30 Billion, Petra Says
-- B y   M o h a m m a d   T a y s e e r
-- 2011-12-29T11:12:54Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-29/jordan-finds-phosphate-reserves-worth-30-billion-petra-says.html
Jordan found about 200 million
metric tons of phosphate reserves of in the northeastern part of
the country, the state-run Petra news agency said.  The reserves have a market value of $30 billion, the news
service reported, citing Bahjat Odwan, president of the
Jordanian Geologists Association. The resource is close to the
surface, making it less expensive to extract, he said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Mohammad Tayseer through the Dubai newsroom at 
